was down 2 million
from its peak

16:31.791 --> 16:35.062
and ad revenues
were down nearly 8%.

16:35.062 --> 16:36.629
I realized the only way

16:36.629 --> 16:38.765
we were going to
beat Penthouse

16:38.765 --> 16:43.636
was to concentrate
on what we did best.

16:43.636 --> 16:46.473
We focused on
sophisticated content,

16:46.473 --> 16:49.809
running the work of great
writers like Norman Mailer

16:49.809 --> 16:51.778
and Kurt Vonnegut...

16:51.778 --> 16:53.513
**

16:53.513 --> 16:56.649
...continuing our tradition
of uncensored interviews

16:56.649 --> 16:58.951
with celebrities
like David Bowie

16:58.951 --> 17:00.487
and Elton John...

17:00.487 --> 17:03.756
* The way the world is,
get just what you can *

17:03.756 --> 17:06.159
And reflecting what
America was talking about.

17:06.159 --> 17:12.365
* Tomorrow, riddled
as a man yeah yeah yeah *

17:12.365 --> 17:15.535
1976 was an election year.

17:15.535 --> 17:17.837
After losing faith
in Richard Nixon

17:17.837 --> 17:19.406
and the Republican
establishment

17:19.406 --> 17:21.174
two years earlier,

17:21.174 --> 17:23.643
many Americans were
looking for a candidate

17:23.643 --> 17:26.313
who could bring about
change in Washington.

17:26.313 --> 17:28.115
One of
the surprise frontrunners

17:28.115 --> 17:30.450
was a peanut farmer
from Georgia

17:30.450 --> 17:32.185
who was
pretty much unknown

17:32.185 --> 17:34.487
before the
Democratic primary.

17:34.487 --> 17:37.590
His name was Jimmy Carter.

17:37.590 --> 17:41.128
1976, Jimmy Carter, going
into the general election

17:41.128 --> 17:43.196
against the sitting
President Gerald Ford.

17:43.196 --> 17:47.367
But Carter was
an Evangelical Baptist

17:47.367 --> 17:50.403
who would occasionally say
that he was born again.

17:50.403 --> 17:52.272
There was a great fear

17:52.272 --> 17:55.308
that he's going to take
his religious values

17:55.308 --> 17:59.546
and now impose them
on the American public.

17:59.546 --> 18:03.082
To counteract that,
Carter's advisors convinced him

18:03.082 --> 18:05.285
to do this interview
for Playboy.

18:05.285 --> 18:07.987
* Everybody knows
everybody goes *

18:07.987 --> 18:10.823
* Make a buck today *

18:10.823 --> 18:14.361
Jimmy Carter
interview, 1976.

18:14.361 --> 18:16.263
The reason it was
such a big deal

18:16.263 --> 18:18.298
is that
a presidential candidate

18:18.298 --> 18:23.470
openly discussed lust
in Playboy magazine.

18:23.470 --> 18:26.873
The media made it
the deal that it was.

18:26.873 --> 18:28.375
We didn't know
how that line,

18:28.375 --> 18:30.777
"adultery in my heart,"
was gonna play,

18:30.777 --> 18:34.581
but that issue
sold 98% at the newsstand.

18:34.581 --> 18:36.516
* Get just what you can *

18:36.516 --> 18:38.718
* Wake up again tomorrow *

18:38.718 --> 18:43.156
No magazine had ever sold
98% at the newsstand before.

18:43.156 --> 18:45.091
**

18:45.091 --> 18:46.793
While everyone
was talking about

18:46.793 --> 18:48.695
what was inside
the magazine,

18:48.695 --> 18:51.631
we also redoubled our
effortsto make Playboy

18:51.631 --> 18:53.933
a force for social
good in the world.

18:53.933 --> 18:57.437
Good evening. In Saigon,
tearful farewells,

18:57.437 --> 18:59.071
but the promise
of a better life

18:59.071 --> 19:01.208
as hundreds of
Vietnamese orphans

19:01.208 --> 19:02.509
today began their journey

19:02.509 --> 19:04.677
toward new homes
in the United States.

19:04.677 --> 19:09.349
* Love is all around me
and so the feeling grows *

19:09.349 --> 19:13.820
The Vietnam war officially
ended in April of 1975,

19:13.820 --> 19:17.690
but it left a humanitarian
crisis in its wake

19:17.690 --> 19:21.160
and I wanted Playboy to
do what it could to help.

19:21.160 --> 19:25.898
I deployed The Big Bunny
and dozens of jet bunnies

19:25.898 --> 19:30.803
to fly Vietnamese orphans
to their new foster homes.

19:30.803 --> 19:36.008
* My mind is made up
by the way that I feel *

19:36.008 --> 19:41.614
In San Francisco, we met
the children with our plane

19:41.614 --> 19:45.618
and they were flown to
various cities in this country.

19:45.618 --> 19:48.255
It was a Playboy baby lift.

19:48.255 --> 19:50.523
* It's written
on the wind *

19:50.523 --> 19:51.924
* It's everywhere I go *

19:51.924 --> 19:53.460
I also wanted to give back

19:53.460 --> 19:56.028
to my new adopted home
of Los Angeles

19:56.028 --> 19:57.564
and the movie industry

19:57.564 --> 20:00.933
that had inspired me
since I was a kid...

20:00.933 --> 20:03.470
**

20:03.470 --> 20:05.672
...so I threw
a fundraiser at the mansion

20:05.672 --> 20:08.808
to preserve
a Hollywood landmark.

20:08.808 --> 20:11.944
* Love sweet love
won't you be good to me? *

20:11.944 --> 20:14.914
The Hollywood sign
was in decay in the '70s,

20:14.914 --> 20:16.783
and he had a fundraiser here.

20:16.783 --> 20:21.321
Lucille Ball, Alice Cooper
both donated money

20:21.321 --> 20:24.056
to have it rebuilt.

20:24.056 --> 20:28.628
* Anybody down
to party down tonight? *

20:28.628 --> 20:34.033
To him, the Hollywood sign
is our Statue of Liberty

20:34.033 --> 20:37.069
or our Eiffel Tower
and what that represents.

20:37.069 --> 20:39.105
**

20:39.105 --> 20:42.775
I felt like Playboy
was getting back on track.

20:42.775 --> 20:45.845
But while our other
ventures may have wavered,

20:45.845 --> 20:48.948
one part of the company
was still thriving.

20:48.948 --> 20:50.082
**

20:50.082 --> 20:52.018
* Get on down *

20:52.018 --> 20:54.821
Victor Lownes'
casino in London.

20:54.821 --> 20:57.690
**

21:03.963 --> 21:05.097
* Get up *

21:05.097 --> 21:07.266
**

21:07.266 --> 21:08.568
Thanks to a weak pound

21:08.568 --> 21:10.102
and steady stream
of oil money

21:10.102 --> 21:12.572
from Middle Eastern sheiks
and businessmen...

21:12.572 --> 21:14.240
* Gotta get up *

21:14.240 --> 21:16.075
...the casino
was bringing in

21:16.075 --> 21:17.477
$26 million annually.

21:17.477 --> 21:18.778
* Get on down *

21:18.778 --> 21:20.146
**

21:20.146 --> 21:24.116
* Gotta get up, gotta
get up, gotta get up *

21:24.116 --> 21:25.785
* Sit on down *

21:25.785 --> 21:28.421
The money that we made
here in London

21:28.421 --> 21:31.458
was supporting the
entire Playboy operation.

21:31.458 --> 21:32.659
**

21:32.659 --> 21:33.960
* Sit on down *

21:33.960 --> 21:36.929
**

21:36.929 --> 21:40.500
Playboy editorial could
get better contributors

21:40.500 --> 21:43.803
as a result,
just with the extra money

21:43.803 --> 21:47.574
that we were plowing
into the main office.

21:47.574 --> 21:50.577
With the success
of the London casino,

21:50.577 --> 21:52.812
Victor began to believe
the rest of Playboy

21:52.812 --> 21:54.447
could recover financially

21:54.447 --> 21:55.982
if we could
duplicate the formula

21:55.982 --> 22:00.687
that worked in London
here in the U.S.

22:00.687 --> 22:03.823
And he knew just
the place to do it.

22:03.823 --> 22:05.825
**

22:05.825 --> 22:07.460
Atlantic City.

22:07.460 --> 22:11.097
**

22:11.097 --> 22:13.299
* Deep in the jungle
where the coconuts grow *

22:13.299 --> 22:15.001
Gambling had
only been legalized

22:14.370 --> 22:17.840
in Atlantic City
since 1974,

22:17.840 --> 22:20.709
and developers were
already buying up land

22:20.709 --> 22:23.679
and starting to build
a casino and resort strip

22:23.679 --> 22:25.581
to rival Las Vegas.

22:25.581 --> 22:29.318
* A monkey over here
monkey over there *

22:29.318 --> 22:31.520
I think it was almost
a natural that Hugh Hefner

22:31.520 --> 22:33.455
would look at Atlantic City
as a great opportunity

22:33.455 --> 22:37.760
to help revive the Playboy
Enterprises company.

22:37.760 --> 22:39.661
The idea was,
we can bring in

22:39.661 --> 22:41.597
a high clientele
of gamblers,

22:41.597 --> 22:43.499
just the way they had
in England,

22:43.499 --> 22:47.436
by offering up this
kind of Playboy experience

22:47.436 --> 22:50.006
and, you know, bringing it
to the Jersey shore.

22:50.006 --> 22:53.810
It's just that I think we
have a real opportunity here.

22:53.810 --> 22:55.577
We have the chance
to establish ourselves

22:55.577 --> 22:58.280
as the premiere casino
in all of the East Coast.

22:58.280 --> 23:00.182
And you don't
anticipate any issues

23:00.182 --> 23:03.585
managing Atlantic City
and London at the same time?

23:03.585 --> 23:04.686
Not at all.

23:04.686 --> 23:05.721
But we do
run the risk

23:05.721 --> 23:07.523
of you being
stretched thin,

23:07.523 --> 23:08.891
and from my experience,

23:08.891 --> 23:10.026
that can lead
to oversights.

23:10.026 --> 23:11.928
Look, Daniels,

23:11.928 --> 23:13.362
I've been doing this
for a while now,

23:13.362 --> 23:16.032
and you're
the new guy, okay?

23:16.032 --> 23:18.367
So, why don't
you just focus

23:18.367 --> 23:20.736
on getting everything
on your end taken care of

23:20.736 --> 23:22.638
and I'll take care
of mine.

23:22.638 --> 23:24.941
How about that?

23:24.941 --> 23:26.809
Victor hasn't
let us down yet.

23:26.809 --> 23:29.812
And I don't intend to.

23:29.812 --> 23:33.782
Fine. I'll get
the ball rolling.

23:33.782 --> 23:35.117
Thanks.

23:43.960 --> 23:46.695
While Victor and
Daniels got started

23:46.695 --> 23:49.098
on our biggest casino yet,

23:49.098 --> 23:51.968
I turned my attention
to an upcoming milestone

23:51.968 --> 23:54.536
for the magazine...

23:54.536 --> 23:57.406
**

24:03.712 --> 24:05.882
...our 25th anniversary.

24:05.882 --> 24:08.951
**

24:11.220 --> 24:13.856
Our January 1979 issue

24:13.856 --> 24:16.225
reflected how far
we'd come

24:16.225 --> 24:19.361
both as a magazine
and as a culture,

24:19.361 --> 24:23.365
from our 1953 cover
with Marilyn Monroe,

24:23.365 --> 24:27.669
when no one was
even talking about sex,

24:27.669 --> 24:30.039
to our fight in court
for freedom of speech

24:30.039 --> 24:31.740
over Jayne Mansfield's
photos,

24:31.740 --> 24:36.078
and our coverage of
civil rights in Vietnam.

24:36.078 --> 24:38.214
The 25th anniversary issue

24:38.214 --> 24:40.049
featured articles
by famous writers

24:40.049 --> 24:44.153
like Shel Silverstein
and Gore Vidal

24:44.153 --> 24:47.289
and an in-depth interview
with Marlon Brando,

24:47.289 --> 24:48.991
but the real centerpiece

24:48.991 --> 24:51.427
of our 25th
anniversary celebration

24:51.427 --> 24:54.030
was The Great
Playmate Hunt.

24:54.030 --> 24:57.099
**

25:02.738 --> 25:05.841
* Never had the pleasure *

25:05.841 --> 25:09.545
* Of loving you *

25:09.545 --> 25:11.513
Over the course
of six months,

25:11.513 --> 25:14.683
we sent out photographers
to 28 American cities

25:14.683 --> 25:17.119
in search of
the most beautiful women

25:17.119 --> 25:18.654
across the country.

25:18.654 --> 25:22.524
* You're everything
that I desire *

25:22.524 --> 25:24.093
The result
was a pictorial

25:24.093 --> 25:26.795
featuring our
16 gorgeous finalists.

25:26.795 --> 25:28.430
**

25:28.430 --> 25:33.235
* All because
you're so unique baby *

25:33.235 --> 25:37.173
* I can't help
but love you girl *

25:37.173 --> 25:40.977
* None can compete
girl with you *

25:40.977 --> 25:43.179
* You *

25:43.179 --> 25:44.380
* Oh oh *

25:44.380 --> 25:45.914
* Ah *

25:45.914 --> 25:49.918
And the winner
of our $25,000 prize

25:49.918 --> 25:53.622
was a 23-year-old
Oklahoma college student

25:53.622 --> 25:55.924
named Candy Stanton.

25:55.924 --> 26:00.997
**

26:02.698 --> 26:05.801
We threw a giant party
to celebrate...

26:05.801 --> 26:09.238
**

26:09.238 --> 26:12.441
...inviting movie stars,

26:12.441 --> 26:16.045
along with much of
Playboy's original staff...

26:16.045 --> 26:17.313
**

26:17.313 --> 26:19.848
...like my old friends
Eldon Sellers

26:19.848 --> 26:21.417
and Vince Tajiri.

26:21.417 --> 26:25.454
Even former Playmate
Janet Pilgrim was on hand.

26:25.454 --> 26:28.024
But the girl that
caught my eye that night

26:28.024 --> 26:29.758
wasn't the winner
of the hunt...

26:29.758 --> 26:31.093
Hi.

26:31.093 --> 26:32.728
...but the runner-up.

26:32.728 --> 26:34.463
Hi.

26:34.463 --> 26:37.766
A 19-year-old
named Dorothy Stratten.

26:37.766 --> 26:39.868
Pictures didn't
do you justice.

26:39.868 --> 26:41.137
Looking at you now,

26:41.137 --> 26:42.971
I don't see
how you didn't win.

26:42.971 --> 26:45.474
Oh. It was
just an honor

26:45.474 --> 26:47.243
to make it
as far as I did.

26:47.243 --> 26:51.080
All of this,
it's incredible

26:51.080 --> 26:52.914
and a little
overwhelming,

26:52.914 --> 26:54.083
to be honest.

26:54.083 --> 26:55.317
Well, you'll have
plenty of time

26:55.317 --> 26:57.053
to get used to it.
I have a feeling

26:57.053 --> 26:58.554
you're gonna
be here a lot.

26:58.554 --> 27:01.357
**

27:01.357 --> 27:04.760
* You're up on
your feet now baby *

27:04.760 --> 27:06.195
**

27:06.195 --> 27:08.664
Dorothy Stratten
was a beautiful,

27:08.664 --> 27:13.135
phenomenal blonde who
came into Playboy's life.

27:13.135 --> 27:15.337
* I know *

27:15.337 --> 27:22.844
She was striking in the most
old-fashioned movie star.

27:22.844 --> 27:24.313
You couldn't believe

27:24.313 --> 27:26.482
that someone was
put together like this.

27:26.482 --> 27:30.519
* Since the day
I met you *

27:30.519 --> 27:32.854
As a young girl,
Dorothy was raised

27:32.854 --> 27:36.024
in a broken home
in Vancouver, Canada.

27:36.024 --> 27:39.128
Dorothy Stratten
grew up in a family

27:39.128 --> 27:42.798
with a single mom
raising three kids.

27:42.798 --> 27:44.933
She worked behind the counter
at the Dairy Queen.

27:44.933 --> 27:47.203
**

27:47.203 --> 27:49.071
It hadn't been
Dorothy's idea

27:49.071 --> 27:51.107
to enter
The Playmate Hunt.

27:51.107 --> 27:54.110
It was her boyfriend,
a man named Paul Snider,

27:54.110 --> 27:55.644
nine years older than her,

27:55.644 --> 27:58.347
who had sent us
her pictures.

27:58.347 --> 28:00.982
Paul Snider
would recruit women

28:00.982 --> 28:03.552
to model in car shows.

28:03.552 --> 28:06.222
He was just trying to
hustle any way he could

28:06.222 --> 28:07.523
to get beautiful women,

28:07.523 --> 28:10.226
so he walked
into the Dairy Queen,

28:10.226 --> 28:11.693
saw Dorothy, you know,

28:11.693 --> 28:13.695
this beautiful woman
behind the counter,

28:13.695 --> 28:15.397
and thought, you know,

28:15.397 --> 28:17.266
this girl is
the girl next door.

28:17.266 --> 28:20.502
Dorothy married Paul

28:20.502 --> 28:23.004
and brought him
with her to L.A.

28:23.004 --> 28:26.308
**

28:35.184 --> 28:37.553
In August of 1979,

28:37.553 --> 28:40.622
we made Dorothy
Playmate of the Month.

28:40.622 --> 28:42.724
**

28:42.724 --> 28:45.594
Her pictorial became
a favorite with readers.

28:45.594 --> 28:51.133
**

28:51.133 --> 28:52.501
We began featuring her

28:52.501 --> 28:54.770
in Playboy
television specials.

28:54.770 --> 28:56.004
Hey, Dorothy's coming.

28:56.004 --> 28:59.908
I'll bet you $100 she'll
pretend not to see me.

28:59.908 --> 29:03.212
She was the most beautiful
girl I'd ever seen.

29:03.212 --> 29:06.548
I was convinced
that in Vancouver,

29:06.548 --> 29:08.184
you know, there's
some mad scientist

29:08.184 --> 29:10.352
working on some kind
of beauty pill.

29:10.352 --> 29:12.854
It was just mindboggling.

29:12.854 --> 29:16.091
**

29:16.091 --> 29:19.094
Her charisma
was undeniable...

29:19.094 --> 29:22.063
**

29:22.063 --> 29:24.533
...and Dorothy soon
used her Playboy celebrity

29:24.533 --> 29:27.169
to start an acting career.

29:27.169 --> 29:31.907
**

29:31.907 --> 29:35.544
Over the next few months,
Dorothy was cast in roles

29:35.544 --> 29:38.247
on the hit TV show
Buck Rogers,

29:38.247 --> 29:40.382
Fantasy Island,

29:40.382 --> 29:43.219
and in the sci-fi movie
Galaxina.

29:43.219 --> 29:45.854
**

29:45.854 --> 29:47.623
But her big break came

29:47.623 --> 29:50.091
when Oscar-winning director
Peter Bogdanovich

29:50.091 --> 29:53.429
cast her in his new movie,
They All Laughed,

29:53.429 --> 29:56.465
alongside John Ritter,
Ben Gazzara,

29:56.465 --> 29:58.133
and Audrey Hepburn.

29:58.133 --> 29:59.768
**

30:01.670 --> 30:03.839
And now, it gives me
a great deal of pleasure

30:03.839 --> 30:07.343
to welcome all of you
here for the presentation

30:07.343 --> 30:09.678
of our 1980
Playmate of the Year,

30:09.678 --> 30:12.581
and she is something
rather special,

30:12.581 --> 30:14.983
Canadian-born
Dorothy Stratten.

30:14.983 --> 30:16.285
Dorothy, you want to
come up here?

30:21.690 --> 30:25.627
I'm sure that this has
been many a girl's dream

30:25.627 --> 30:28.897
and certainly many of
the Playmates' dream,

30:28.897 --> 30:30.332
and it's been mine.

30:32.634 --> 30:35.737
Dorothy's star
was on the rise...

30:35.737 --> 30:37.038
**

30:37.038 --> 30:38.740
...but no one suspected

30:38.740 --> 30:43.912
that her personal life
would begin to haunt her.

30:43.912 --> 30:45.914
What is it?

30:45.914 --> 30:48.584
Uh, it's Paul.

30:48.584 --> 30:51.520
He's at the front gate,
demanding to be let in.

30:51.520 --> 30:55.857
Oh, my gosh. I told him
this was just...

30:55.857 --> 30:57.826
Is he causing
a scene or...?

30:57.826 --> 30:59.261
No, they would have
called the police.

30:59.261 --> 31:00.629
He's just
refusing to leave.

31:00.629 --> 31:02.898
Dorothy, if you
need me to do anything...

31:02.898 --> 31:04.800
No, no. It's fine.

31:05.867 --> 31:08.904
Here is this guy
that discovered her,

31:08.904 --> 31:12.974
and all of a sudden,
now she's in movies.

31:12.974 --> 31:17.145
She's Playmate of the Year.
Her career is blossoming.

31:17.145 --> 31:18.680
**

31:18.680 --> 31:22.384
I think he started
really losing it

31:22.384 --> 31:24.820
and getting paranoid
like he's losing her.

31:26.522 --> 31:28.857
I was proud of Dorothy

31:28.857 --> 31:30.926
and glad she was
leaving for New York

31:30.926 --> 31:36.432
to shoot Bogdanovich's
film without Paul.

31:36.432 --> 31:37.933
Let's hear it
for Hef! Hey!

31:40.669 --> 31:42.471
Around the same time,

31:42.471 --> 31:44.473
one of my own dreams
was coming true.

31:44.473 --> 31:46.542
We have a ceremony today

31:46.542 --> 31:50.211
for the 1,716th star

31:50.211 --> 31:52.213
to be placed
in the Walk of Fame.

31:56.685 --> 31:58.820
Those of you
who know me best

31:58.820 --> 32:03.892
know what a very,
very special day today is.

32:03.892 --> 32:09.230
I have chosen to make
Southern California my home.

32:09.230 --> 32:10.832
This town, the dreams
that are created,

32:10.832 --> 32:12.534
the films that
are created,

32:12.534 --> 32:14.603
undoubtedly have
more influence on me

32:14.603 --> 32:17.138
than any other single
factor in my life,

32:17.138 --> 32:20.075
and I just want you to know
that it means more to me

32:20.075 --> 32:21.477
than a Pulitzer Prize.

32:21.477 --> 32:23.679
Thank you very much.
I mean it.

32:26.348 --> 32:30.285
I was honored to be a real
part of Hollywood history,

32:30.285 --> 32:32.153
something I'd dreamt about

32:32.153 --> 32:35.056
since I was a kid
growing up in Chicago.

32:35.056 --> 32:39.661
But while I was receiving
accolades, I had no idea

32:39.661 --> 32:42.097
